memberdef.name: stl_declare_iterator
memberdef.initializer: typedef struct \ { \ size_t current; \ size_t lenght; \ type *buffer; \ } __stl_t(type, it); \ __stl_t(type, it) __stl_fn(type, __base_name, it_init)(type * buffer, size_t lenght); \ const type *__stl_fn(type, __base_name, it_next)(__stl_t(type, it) * it);

memberdef.name: stl_implement_iterator
memberdef.initializer: __stl_t(type, it) __stl_fn(type, __base_name, it_init)(type * buffer, size_t lenght) \ { \ return (__stl_t(type, it)){.current = 0, .lenght = lenght, .buffer = buffer}; \ } \ const type *__stl_fn(type, __base_name, it_next)(__stl_t(type, it) * it) \ { \ if (it->current < it->lenght) \ { \ type *v = &(it->buffer[it->current]); \ it->current++; \ return v; \ } \ return NULL; \ }
